{{Infobox language |name=Mbule |region=southwestern [[Cameroon]] |ethnicity=[[Yambassa people|Yambassa]] |speakers=110 |date=2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Mbam languages|Mbam]] |fam6=Yambasa |iso3=mlb |glotto=mbul1262 |glottorefname=Mbule |guthrie=A.623 }}
'''Mbule''', also called '''Dumbule''' or '''Mbola''', is an endangered [[Southern Bantoid]] language spoken by a few people in central [[Cameroon]].
The language is spoken in [[Mbola, Cameroon|Mbola]] village in the South [[Bokito, Cameroon|Bokito]] commune, [[Mbam-et-Inoubou]] department of the [[Centre Region, Cameroon]]. As reported in 2009, there were just 110 speakers of the languages, none of whom were monolingual.<ref name=e18/>
