{{Infobox language |name=Safene |nativename=Saafi-Saafi |states=[[Senegal]] |ethnicity=[[Saafi people]] |speakers=200,000 |date=2012 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Senegambian languages|Senegambian]] |fam4=[[Cangin languages|Cangin]] |iso3=sav |glotto=saaf1238 |glottorefname=Saafi-Saafi |script=[[Latin script|Latin]], [[Arabic script|Arabic]]<ref name="e18"/> }} {{infobox ethnonym |Saafi |Saafici |Saafi-Saafi |Safene }} '''Safene''' (''Saafen''), or '''Saafi-Saafi''', is the principal [[Cangin language]], spoken by 200,000 people in [[Senegal]]. Speakers are heavily concentrated in the area surrounding [[Dakar]], particularly in the [[Thies Region]].
