'''Temiar''' is a Central Aslian ([[Mon–Khmer]]) language spoken in Western [[Malaysia]] by the [[Temiar people]].  The Temiar are one of the larger Aslian-speaking peoples, numbering around 30,000 in 2017.{{cn|date=December 2017}}

